PROBLEM STATEMENT:
A message has been encrypted using RSA. 
The public key is gone… but someone might have been careless with the private key. Can you recover it and decrypt the message?

HINTS:
Metadata can tell you more than you expect.
Hex can be turned back into a key file.

APPROACH:
I am provided with the encrypted flag and an image file which has a key image
The metadata gave me a long hex string as comment
I converted into the private key format and verified
I used this key against the encrypted flag.enc file 
Got the flag.
